Starice::

Starice was waitting that baby ended to eat. She didn't know any 
lullaby so she continued talking with the baby with a sweet tone 
while she cradled her, it seemed calm her down. As soon as baby ended 
to drink the milk she would retired the baby's bottle and would find 
a place to let baby sleep... "humm" thought the femme "maybe she will 
need an apropiate bed... well -a baby's bed..."



--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Moon Mist" <shadowwarrior_ax@h...> wrote:
> 
> She ate soundly, her tiny paws working against the sides of the 
bottle like 
> they would against mommy's side to get the milk out. Her itty claws 
clicked 
> at the sides, feeling warmer when Starice spread her wings and 
cradled her 
> in them.
> The soft wings reminded her of mommy's fur and with the warm milk 
it was 
> almost the exact same, the only things different is that the milk 
tasted 
> different and she couldn't smell mommy's scent.
> But she kept on eating, making little sucking sounds as she lowered 
the 
> level of milk in the bottle.
> The sounds of Starice's voice was comforting to her, soothing her 
with its 
> sweet tone.
> She was almost ready for sleep, and her paws left the bottle, 
moving slowly 
> in tiny movements as she suckled.
> So tiny, so soft and innocent. A round, rolly-polly puppy.
>
